{
  "question_id": "question-001",
  "title": "Margin of Error",
  "difficulty": "Easy",
  "question_text": "<div class=\"paragraph\">A local news station was covering a city council race and said that Candidate <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$A$</span> was polling ahead of Candidate <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$B$</span> with <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$52\\%$</span> of voters favoring Candidate <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$A$</span>. The news station also stated their results come with a margin of error of <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$3\\%$</span>. </div><div class=\"paragraph\">What is believed to be the true proportion of voters who favor Candidate <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$A$</span>?</div>",
  "image_files": [],
  "choices": [
    {
      "letter": "A",
      "text": "Somewhere between\n49\n%\nand\n55\n%"
    },
    {
      "letter": "B",
      "text": "Exactly\n52\n%"
    },
    {
      "letter": "C",
      "text": "Less than\n52\n%"
    },
    {
      "letter": "D",
      "text": "More than\n52\n%"
    },
    {
      "letter": "E",
      "text": "Less the\n49\n%\nbut greater than\n55\n%"
    }
  ],
  "correct_answer": "<strong>Choice 'A'</strong> is the correct answer. ",
  "solution": "When a random sample is taken, the sample proportion will rarely equal the true population proportion. In this case, the sample proportion produced a <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-16929-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mrow class=&quot;MJX-TeXAtom-ORD&quot;><mover><mi>p</mi><mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;>&amp;#x005E;</mo></mover></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0.52</mn></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90971\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90972\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90973\" class=\"mjx-texatom\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90974\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90975\" class=\"mjx-munderover\"><span class=\"mjx-stack\"><span class=\"mjx-over\" style=\"height: 0.213em; padding-bottom: 0.06em; padding-left: 0.085em;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90977\" class=\"mjx-mo\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.332em;\">^</span></span></span><span class=\"mjx-op\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90976\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I\" style=\"padding-top: 0.222em; padding-bottom: 0.496em;\">p</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90978\" class=\"mjx-mo MJXc-space3\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.058em; padding-bottom: 0.332em;\">=</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90979\" class=\"mjx-mn MJXc-space3\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">0.52</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\"><mover><mi>p</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">^</mo></mover></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0.52</mn></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-16929\">\\hat{p} = 0.52%</script></span> or <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-16930-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mn>52</mn><mi mathvariant=&quot;normal&quot;>&amp;#x0025;</mi></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90980\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90981\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90982\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">52</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90983\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.441em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">%</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>52</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-16930\">52\\%</script></span>. But, this value came with a margin of error, so the news station does believes that the value of <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-16931-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mn>52</mn><mi mathvariant=&quot;normal&quot;>&amp;#x0025;</mi></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90984\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90985\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90986\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">52</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90987\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.441em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">%</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>52</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-16931\">52\\%</script></span> is a good starting point, but might not be exactly correct. The news station believes the true population proportion will be: \n\n<span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-16932-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mn>52</mn><mi mathvariant=&quot;normal&quot;>&amp;#x0025;</mi><mo>&amp;#x00B1;</mo><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=&quot;normal&quot;>&amp;#x0025;</mi></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90988\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90989\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90990\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">52</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90991\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.441em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">%</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90992\" class=\"mjx-mo MJXc-space2\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.332em;\">±</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90993\" class=\"mjx-mn MJXc-space2\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">3</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90994\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.441em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">%</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>52</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi><mo>±</mo><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-16932\">52\\% \\pm 3\\%</script></span>\n\nTherefore, they believe the true proportion who favor candidate <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-16933-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mi>A</mi></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90995\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90996\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90997\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I\" style=\"padding-top: 0.496em; padding-bottom: 0.277em;\">A</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-16933\">A</script></span> to be somewhere between <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-16934-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mn>49</mn><mi mathvariant=&quot;normal&quot;>&amp;#x0025;</mi></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90998\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-90999\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91000\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">49</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91001\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.441em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">%</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>49</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-16934\">49\\%</script></span> and <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-16935-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mn>55</mn><mi mathvariant=&quot;normal&quot;>&amp;#x0025;</mi></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91002\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91003\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91004\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">55</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91005\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.441em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">%</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>55</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-16935\">55\\%</script></span>\n\n<strong>Choice 'A'</strong> is correct. ",
  "distractor_explanations": {
    "B": "<strong>Choice 'B'</strong> is incorrect. As stated above, the sample proportion rarely equals the population proportion, and since they stated a margin of error, they don't believe it to be exactly <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-16936-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mn>52</mn><mi mathvariant=&quot;normal&quot;>&amp;#x0025;</mi></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91006\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91007\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91008\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">52</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91009\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.441em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">%</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>52</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-16936\">52\\%</script></span>",
    "C": "<strong>Choice 'C'</strong> is incorrect. The margin of error needs to be added and subtracted from the estimate to create an interval of possible values. ",
    "D": "<strong>Choice 'D'</strong> is incorrect. The margin of error needs to be added and subtracted from the estimate to create an interval of possible values. ",
